Market women and members of Arewa community in Lagos weekend staged a solidarity rally for President Muhammadu Buhari’s his re-election. Executive Director, Lagos International Trade Fair Complex, Mrs Lucy Ajayi, who led the rally with representatives of other ethnic groups and traders, said:  “Our market women, our Arewa brothers and every other person you are seeing here are simply saying, four more years for President Buhari.” Chairman, Arewa Community, Lagos State, Alhaji Muhammed Dandama Yabo,  said all his members had collected their Permanent Voter’s Cards and would vote for Buhari and the APC governorship candidate in Lagos State, Babajide  Sanwo-Olu. The Iyaloja General, Ikosi/Isheri Local Council Development Area, Madam Iyabo Ahmed, said market women decided to support Buhari and Sanwo-Olu because their political leader, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, had directed them to do so. APC group mobilises support for Buhari, Sanwo-Olu Arewa Lagos endorses Buhari, Sanwo-Olu, other APC candidates Osinbajo in closed-door meeting with Arewa community leader in Lagos